Nov 15 2009 	superb value perfect for family city trip	We booked out stay at the Columbus only 24 hours before our stay when we took our 4 year old son for a trip to London to see the sights, Aquarium, London Eye, Hamleys, Christmas Lights etc. We wanted somewhere central, near a tube/bus stop near the sights.We found the Columbus having been astonished how much the chains, Travelodge, Premier Inn, Holiday Inn etc wanted for just one night with some not including any breakfast in their rates. It was perfect for what we wanted. Yes, its not luxurious but neither are the budget hotel chains but it was totally adeqaute for us.Comfortable double and single bed, with room between them, showeroom was very clean (yet cosy) - one at a time only.Breakfast was included and was made up of tea, coffee, juices, bread, toaster, croissant, rolls, cheese, ham, cereals, yoghurt, fruit, jams and chocolate spread (loved by our 4 year old on his toast)For food in the evening we went to the Swan pub round the corner, welcomed our four year old (although they did not do child portions for food they supplied plate for us to share our dinner with him) where we had a great meal before heading to see the Xmas lightsNext morning, Hyde Park only 3-4 minute walk away for refreshing strollIf you have concerns about booking with an independent hotel rather than a chain, (like we did) then rest assured, the Columbus is just as good as any we have stayed in.	
Jul 2 2009 	no lift	this hotel was a value considering the location. Had easy walk to Hyde Park and Paddington station. We stayed in a quad room and the bathroom seemed to be taken from a cruise ship. You needed to step up into the bathroom which may cause a barrier for some. The water temp was okay, we had no problems. Our room faced the street and since there was no AC we needed to leave the screen less window open all nite and the traffic only stopped for about an hour..3 to 4 am. The steps were the low point. For being on the 3rd floor it seemed like climbing up a tower. The staff however did offer to carry our luggage up the day we checked in. The staff were very congenial and accommodating. They were helpful in arranging transportation and giving tourist info. Would recommend this hotel but just be ready to walk the steps. The breakfast was nice but was the same thing every morning we stayed for 4 days. Had cheese,ham,fruits,cereal and juices.	
