Nov 23 2007 	Convenient Area Try a different hotel	The hotel and area of Paddington are very convenient. The Heathrow Express train goes to Paddington and the hotel is a few blocks from the station. A tube station is located there as well, some restaurants and pubs and Hyde park are all close. The hotel itself was fair. The room was dated, but clean. It did lose water for half of one day and hot water for most of the day. We fortunately arose early and showered before the water was lost and did not need hot water during the day. The hotel is not staffed at night and our key did not let us in the front door. After a night out we had to trek to another hotel and the attendent was not very helpful in aiding us in a timely fashion. We had to make several attempts for him to go to our hotel to let us in. There are many hotels in paddington. The area was very convenient for sightseeing and tube accessibility. We would look elsewhere for another hotel.	
Nov 2 2007	Wouldn't Go Back	I have to say we were disappointed with the Columbus Hotel. We had a quad room for 2 nights in July 2007. We were prepared for a basic, tiny room and even knew about the stairs, but we did want something clean. Sadly, we didn't get that. The room was dirty--an empty bottle on the floor, stopped-up sink, and I don't even want to talk about the rest of the bathroom. The management was nice about trying to fix things, but didn't quite manage to do so. It took them an entire day to unstop the sink and they never did get the room any cleaner. On the other hand, they did give us a small discount after we complained several times. That said, we really liked staying in the Paddington area. Lots of restaurants, two tube stops within walking distance, Hyde Park a few blocks away. I definitely would stay near Paddington station again, just not in the Columbus Hotel.	
