Jul 7 2005 	Excellent basic sleep space	Like the prior review says, there are scores of small hotels near Paddington -- and using one is a great way to stay in London if you are paying the bill yourself. Just take the LHR express, walk to the hotel, dump your stuff, see London, and come back to sleep. Very efficient. Columbus is a very good choice among them - friendly staff, rooms small but adequate, breakfast fine, clean, quiet -- and very good value for money. I've stayed multiple times and been satisfied each time.	
Apr 30 2004	Simple basic all about location	This is one of the many places to stay on Sussex near Paddington. Okay if you just want a bed to fall into after a full day of sight-seeing. Look elsewhere if you require luxury. Cereals, croissant, fruit, coffee &amp; tea are included in the rate. Room includes inserted bathroom similar to those found in RV's. The toilet, sink and shower are all combined so expect everything to get wet. Service requests were not attended to during our stay. Our credit card was not billed until 3 months after our vacation! It was great being able to walk to/from Paddington Station to take the Heathrow Express (only 15 min. to airport). Handy if there's a taxi strike. Hyde Park is perfect for early morning exercise. Check out The Swan pub on Bayswater Rd. for lunch and the little Indian restaurant on Bathurst St. for dinner. Just use the tall Royal Lancaster Hotel as a landmark!	
